<topic id="d1e59"><title>Exercise 3.3</title><body><p>
<b>Express the square of the component of
<d4p_eqn_inline>
    <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
  </d4p_eqn_inline> in the direction of
<d4p_eqn_inline>
    <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
  </d4p_eqn_inline> in terms of dot products.</b>
</p><p>
Solution:
</p><p>
By
<b>
  <ph outputclass="a">definition</ph>
</b>
this square is 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mo>|</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:msup><m:mo>|</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mi>cos</m:mi><m:mo>⁡</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 where 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mi>θ</m:mi></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 is the angle between 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 and 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
, which is 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:mrow></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
.
</p></body></topic>